00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:04,800
God called them to turn back.

496
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:06,800
What was God's will?

497
00:23:06,800 --> 00:23:07,800
In the 14th chapter, verse 3,

498
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:09,800
God said, "And Pharaoh said,

499
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:14,800
 'The Israelites were lost on the ground,

500
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:17,800
and the wilderness had trapped them.'

501
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:19,800
 In the 14th chapter,

502
00:23:19,800 --> 00:23:22,800
God said, "I will make Pharaoh's heart strong,

503
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:24,800
and he will chase them.

504
00:23:24,800 --> 00:23:26,800
And then I will be glorified

505
00:23:26,800 --> 00:23:30,800
in Pharaoh and his whole army."

506
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:33,800
The Egyptians knew that they were in the wilderness.

507
00:23:33,800 --> 00:23:36,800
So the Israelites walked on.

508
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:39,800
God's command seems to be very complicated.

509
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:41,800
It's not humanly reasonable.

510
00:23:41,800 --> 00:23:44,800
But what is the ultimate goal?

511
00:23:44,800 --> 00:23:47,800
It is to be glorified to God.

512
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:51,800
God's purpose is not to make us feel sad and empty.

513
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:53,800
It's not that people think

514
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:56,800
they are doing well and that's it.

515
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:58,800
God's command is needed

516
00:23:58,800 --> 00:24:02,800
to make us learn to trust Him.

517
00:24:02,800 --> 00:24:03,800
 At the beginning, we said that

518
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:06,800
there are many changes in life.

519
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:08,800
 Especially in the pandemic,

520
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:12,800
we have encountered many unideal situations.

521
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:16,800
 We all want to go to an ideal place.

522
00:24:16,800 --> 00:24:18,800
 We always say that we don't like this situation,

523
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:20,800
don't like this place,

524
00:24:20,800 --> 00:24:22,800
don't like this context.

525
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:24,800
 So we want to walk away.

526
00:24:24,800 --> 00:24:26,800
 We think that's OK.

527
00:24:26,800 --> 00:24:28,800
 Of course, this is humanly reasonable.

528
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:31,800
 But this story seems to tell us

529
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:35,800
what is the most important thing in God's eyes.

530
00:24:35,800 --> 00:24:38,800
 The most important thing is not what we think.

531
00:24:38,800 --> 00:24:41,800
 Everything is fine and good.

532
00:24:41,800 --> 00:24:43,800
 In chapter 14, verse 30,

533
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:47,800
 it says, "On that day, Jehovah saved the Israelites

534
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:49,800
and took the hands of the Egyptians."

535
00:24:49,800 --> 00:24:53,800
 It says that they crossed the Red Sea.

536
00:24:53,800 --> 00:24:55,800
 What did the Israelites see?

537
00:24:55,800 --> 00:24:57,800
 They saw Jehovah's victory.

538
00:24:57,800 --> 00:24:59,800
 What did the Israelites see?

539
00:24:59,800 --> 00:25:03,800
 They saw Jehovah's great deeds to the Egyptians.

540
00:25:03,800 --> 00:25:05,800
 They knew how to glorify Him,

541
00:25:05,800 --> 00:25:10,800
 how to trust God and His divine power.

542
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:14,800
 When we encounter difficulties,

543
00:25:14,800 --> 00:25:20,800
 we think that we are leaving this unideal situation.

544
00:25:20,800 --> 00:25:23,800
 We are looking for an ideal place.

545
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:28,800
 If God really wants to lead us to our ultimate goal,

546
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:32,800
 without disasters, without worries, without sickness,

547
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:36,800
 we can retire and live happily,

548
00:25:36,800 --> 00:25:41,800
 I think God is the most unsuccessful prophet.

549
00:25:41,800 --> 00:25:46,800
 The most successful one should be Jehovah.

550
00:25:46,800 --> 00:25:48,800
 Because in the Egyptian Empire,

551
00:25:48,800 --> 00:25:52,800
 if you put your trust in Him, you can live in peace.

552
00:25:52,800 --> 00:25:54,800
 So, you see, when the Israelites left Egypt,

553
00:25:54,800 --> 00:25:59,800
 they were not able to enjoy their eternal peace.

554
00:25:59,800 --> 00:26:02,800
 In fact, after the Israelites left Egypt,

555
00:26:02,800 --> 00:26:06,800
 they crossed the Red Sea and the Sea of ​​Grass.

556
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:09,800
 It was a trial.

557
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:13,800
 Because God's purpose was to prepare us

558
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:17,800
 to become a group of people who were faithful to His will.

559
00:26:17,800 --> 00:26:20,800
 This is the greatest blessing.

560
00:26:20,800 --> 00:26:23,800
 The greatest blessing is not that we have no disasters, no sickness,

561
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:25,800
 no epidemic.

562
00:26:25,800 --> 00:26:28,800
 The greatest blessing is that we can become the children of God,

563
00:26:28,800 --> 00:26:30,800
 and be with Him.

564
00:26:30,800 --> 00:26:32,800
 We can be so glorious

565
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:36,800
 that we can become people who serve God.

566
00:26:36,800 --> 00:26:38,800
 We are now facing different disasters.

567
00:26:38,800 --> 00:26:41,800
 Whether it is an epidemic or a downturn in life,

568
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:43,800
 we may need to ask

569
00:26:43,800 --> 00:26:46,800
 whether we will still be loyal to God

570
00:26:46,800 --> 00:26:49,800
 after these disasters and downturns.

571
00:26:49,800 --> 00:26:51,800
 We just need to be there to answer the call.

572
00:26:51,800 --> 00:26:55,800
 We have not learned to be more faithful to God.

573
00:26:55,800 --> 00:26:58,800
 Or when we have passed the command of God,

574
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:00,800
 we will be more faithful to God.

575
00:27:00,800 --> 00:27:04,800
 Personally, the same is true for the Church.

576
00:27:04,800 --> 00:27:08,800
 God said, "Do not waste the path He has led us on."

577
00:27:08,800 --> 00:27:11,800
 No matter what the disaster is,

578
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:13,800
 let us, the Church,

579
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:15,800
 be able to experience new lessons.

580
00:27:15,800 --> 00:27:16,800
 Let us, the Church,

581
00:27:16,800 --> 00:27:20,800
 become a Church that is more in line with His will.

582
00:27:20,800 --> 00:27:22,800
 Some scholars said it was very interesting.

583
00:27:22,800 --> 00:27:25,800
 They said, "The main thing that God wants to do in the Exodus

584
00:27:25,800 --> 00:27:29,800
 is to take Israelite out of Egypt."

